# Supabase — create a project at https://supabase.com
# Then run migrations in supabase/migrations/ via the SQL editor.
#
# Where to find these values (new Supabase dashboard):
#   Project URL  → Integrations → Data API → copy the API URL and remove "/rest/v1/"
#   API key      → Settings → API Keys → Publishable or legacy anon key
#
# Put this file at the project ROOT (not src/). Vite does not read src/.env.

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-publishable-or-anon-key

# --- Supabase dashboard setup (Authentication) ---
#
# 1. Email provider → minimum password length: 10
#    → required: lowercase + uppercase + digits
#    → enable leaked password protection (HaveIBeenPwned)
#
# 2. Multi-Factor → enable TOTP
#
# 3. Google provider → enable, add OAuth client ID/secret from Google Cloud Console
#    → Authorized redirect URI: https://<project-ref>.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
#    → Add Site URL + http://localhost:5173 to Redirect URLs (Authentication → URL Configuration)
#
# 4. URL Configuration → Site URL: http://localhost:5173 (dev)
#
# 5. Storage → run supabase/migrations/004_vehicle_photos_storage.sql
#    (enables browse/paste image uploads on Fleet → Add car)
#
# --- Vercel CLI deploy (Flex business account, no GitHub required) ---
#
# Auth option A — device login (incognito → flexmanagementgroup@gmail.com):
#   vercel logout && vercel login
#
# Auth option B — token (do NOT use vercel login --token; that flag is invalid):
#   export VERCEL_TOKEN="your-token-from-vercel-settings-tokens"
#   vercel whoami   # confirms which account the token belongs to
#
# Then link and deploy (replace ANON_KEY with the value from this file):
#   vercel link --yes --scope flex26
#   vercel env add VITE_SUPABASE_URL production --value "https://your-project-ref.supabase.co" --yes --scope flex26
#   vercel env add VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY production --value "ANON_KEY" --yes --scope flex26
#   (repeat env add for preview and development if needed)
#   vercel --prod --yes --scope flex26
#
# Supabase → Authentication → URL Configuration:
#   Site URL: https://your-app.vercel.app
#   Redirect URLs: https://your-app.vercel.app/**
